Maclean Hunter to Issue Stock
Maclean Hunter said the net proceeds of about C$173
million will be used to help pay down its total debt, which
was C$635.2 million in early December. The offering by the
Toronto-based publishing, printing and broadcasting concern
is expected to be completed by the end of February.
   In trading on the Toronto Stock Exchange yesterday,
Maclean Hunter common shares closed at C$12.00, down 75
Canadian cents.